'''Rear Guard''' (military definition) Security detachment that protects the rear of a column from hostile forces. During a withdrawal, it delays the enemy by armed resistance, destroying bridges, and blocking roads. (United States Military Dictionary)[http://www.angelfire.com/mi2/angela764/military/military_dictionary.html] 

Rearguard (broadly) An economic, political, or social resistance, ''e.g.'', mounting a rear-guard effort to prevent tax increases.
Also, an entrenched or conservative element, as in a political party
 
antonyms - vanguard, avant-garde